Introduction

GsA (an acronym for Girls' Alert) was a South Korean girl group formed by Roots Entertainment. They debuted on May 25, 2017, with their first single "Dreamgirls."

On April 24, 2020, Roots Entertainment announced the termination of all members' contracts due to the company's worsening situation caused by the COVID-19 outbreak. However, they clarified that the group had not disbanded, and Jisung, Seulbi, and Gooseul would continue as a trio while Saetbyeol would start anew with a different group and agency.

On April 27, 2020, Roots Entertainment reversed their decision and signed renewal contracts with the remaining members of GsA. The group officially disbanded in mid-2023.
